org.llrp.ltk.generated.custom.parameters

Class ImpinjBlockPermalock

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.llrp.ltk.types.LLRPParameter
      • org.llrp.ltk.types.TLVParameter
        • org.llrp.ltk.generated.parameters.Custom
          • org.llrp.ltk.generated.custom.parameters.ImpinjBlockPermalock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AccessCommandOpSpec, AccessCommandOpSpecResult, SpecParameter

    public class ImpinjBlockPermalock
extends Custom
implements AccessCommandOpSpec
    This custom parameter is an OpSpec that configures the C1G2 BlockPermalock status of a particular memory bank from a tag. The AccessPassword field is the password required to move the tag into the secured state if needed. See also
